MENINGITIS, UNDIAGNOSED ILLNESS - NIGERIA: (KATSINA) FATAL, SCHOOLCHILDREN, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
***************************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Wed 21 Mar 2018 2:00AM
Source: Daily Trust [edited]
https://www.dailytrust.com.ng/kurfi-school-deaths-parent-demands-explanation.html


A parent whose child was among those killed by yet to be identified disease that broke out at Government Science Secondary School [SS] in Kurfi has demanded explanation for the cause of his son's death. [The father], whose son, a 13 year old, was among the 8 that died, said, "We are being kept in the dark as to what was wrong before the death. I have reached out to the authorities and doctors to know the cause to no avail."

[The father] said although the dead could not be returned to life, knowing the cause of death could check future occurrences and calm the tensed atmosphere especially with parents whose children were in the affected school. "It's worrisome that we are still being kept in the dark. I have another child in the school," he said. Speaking of the late [son], [the father] said, "My son took ill overnight. He had severe body temperature and was rushed to the hospital the next day. I was with him as he kept holding his stomach. A doctor examined him and prescribed some drugs which were sent for. Before the medicines came, my son died in my presence."

Up till press time, the executive secretary of the Science Schools Management Board, Lawal Bosa, under whose purview the school is, had failed to respond to enquiries made to him. It could be recalled that an outbreak of a strange disease at the Government Science Secondary School Kurfi killed 8 students, prompting a closure of the school [Is this a separate event? - Mod.SH].

[byline: Habibu Umar Aminu]

